## Migration: Old → New Variable Structure

When refactoring from old tokens to new, use this mapping:

| Old token | New token | Notes |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| `--base-1` | `--bg-base-default` | Primary surfaces (cards, modals, panels) |
| `--base-2` | `--bg-base-secondary` | Page background, negative space |
| `--base-3` | `--bg-base-tertiary` | Tertiary surfaces, dividers |
| `--base-4` | `--bg-base-tertiary` or `--text-disabled-default` | Input fills, disabled surfaces |
| `--base-5` | `--border-base-default` | Borders |
| `--teal` | `--bg-brand-default` / `--text-brand-default` / `--border-brand-default` | Per context (fill, text, border) |
| `--teal-t1`, `--teal-t2` | `--bg-brand-tertiary` | Hover, selected states |
| `--text-primary` | `--text-base-default` | Primary text |
| `--text-secondary` | `--text-base-secondary` | Secondary text |
| `--text-tertiary`, `--text-muted` | `--text-base-secondary` | Muted text |
| `--text-disabled` | `--text-disabled-default` | Disabled text |
| `--gray-1` … `--gray-9` | Use semantic tokens above | Do not use primitives directly in components |

### Migration rules
1. Replace `--base-1` with `--bg-base-default` for surfaces.
2. Replace `--base-5` with `--border-base-default` for borders.
3. Replace `--teal` with `--bg-brand-default` (fills), `--text-brand-default` (text/icons), or `--border-brand-default` (borders).
4. Replace `--teal-t1` / `--teal-t2` with `--bg-brand-tertiary` for selected/hover.
5. Replace `--text-primary` with `--text-base-default`.
6. Replace `--text-secondary` with `--text-base-secondary`.
7. Use `--bg-danger-default`, `--bg-success-default`, `--bg-warning-default` for semantic fills; `--text-danger-default`, `--text-success-default`, `--text-warning-default` for semantic text; `--border-danger-default` for error borders.

