## Design System Setup

### globals.css
- Define CSS variables for light/dark per `[data-theme="light"]` and `[data-theme="dark"]`.
- Use token values from design-system-tokens.mdc (derived from [Figma Foundations](https://www.figma.com/design/AW4jk9SLPKlSqYt6NZ1QK5/Qure-%3C%3E-Figma-Design-system?node-id=9762-187&p=f&m=dev)).
- Map semantic tokens to primitives; never hardcode hex in components.

### Tailwind config
- Extend theme with token references: `colors: { base: { 1: 'var(--bg-base-default)', ... }, ... }`.
- No hardcoded values; use `var(--token-name)` or arbitrary values `bg-[var(--bg-base-default)]`.

### ThemeProvider
- Set `data-theme` on `<html>`: `light` (default) or `dark`.
- Persist preference to localStorage; optionally respect `prefers-color-scheme`.

### New project checklist
1. Copy `.cursor/rules/` to new repo.
2. Create `globals.css` with token definitions.
3. Add Tailwind config extending tokens.
4. Add ThemeProvider wrapping app.
5. Verify all tokens match Figma foundations.
